defaultT
defaulthe difficulty is in the big cities is probably the mix of how we travel is wrong. We need to encourage people to cycle and therefore we need to make the roads safe, and to do that you have to plan, not just one year, it's year on year, it's decade on 
defaultdecade, and other cities manage to do it, and we could do it too. It's very difficult to change the road layout for cyclists in a matter of months; it does take a long time planning, and it can be done, and it's done effectively across Europe.
defaultSo that's t
defaulthe first practical step you would take, just to try to encourage people to get out of their cars and onto bicycles?
defaultIt only needs people on the margin: the people who are more likely to do it, to encourage them. Of course there are people who won't do it 
defaultwhatever, but if enough people do it, it does make a change. We're talking about things on the margin. 
default(Interview with Andrew Davis, 
defaultDirector of the Environmental Travel Association, 
defaulton BBC Radio Five Live)
