defaultOkay, so the basic strategy is as follows: 
defaultplan, study and then “introduce” a cycle network
default. O
defaultnce it is up and running, develop it further “on the basis of priorit
defaulty interventions and a timetable
default”
default.
default This strategy is still running its course in the Netherlands
default (the Dutch program these things to work i
defaultn twe
defaultnty-year cycles, I believe
default)
default. It is absolutely the tried and tested method, and it is incredibly frustrating that people here consistently find ways to misunderstand it.
default&#xa0;
default“Oh, we’ve tried all that!” 
defaultsome of them
default say, confusing a 
defaultcycle network which fun
defaultctions at a 
defaultminimum level as “more of the same”. But actually it’s a means to an end, a stepping-stone. The eastern philosophers talk about going from zero to one as being the hardest step, and in this case, ‘one’
default is a comprehensive, city-wide
default cycle networ
defaultk
default. Once the network has been ma
defaultde to work, once it is functioning
default,
default once it is up and running, 
defaultgoing from one to two, from two to three, from three to four, and so on,
default would be
default relatively quite easy. By the time you 
defaultneed to 
defaultgo from six to seven, you find th
defaultat 
defaultyou can skip along
default. But without a solid foundation, 
defaultit’s very difficult to build upwards
default in any sort of meaningful way
default.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe case is, there isn’t a single town or city in this country which has a functioning cycle network, so how can people say this 
defaultapproach has been tried before?
default&#xa0;
defaultJust a few words about a network introduced to the point where
default it functions. I
defaultt is of paramount importance that cyclists are visible to motor traffic.
default 
defaultThis 
defaultdoes not mean hi-viz; rather it 
defaultmeans th
defaultat cyclists 
defaulthave to be posi
defaulttioned in the correct place relative to 
defaulteveryone else
default. 
defaultFor example, r
defaultesearch from Denmark suggests that the 'bike box' should be at least five metres deep (so that lorry drivers have a direct view of any cyclists who may be waiting ahead of them).
default&#xa0;
defaultStressing that I am talking here about short-term solutions, another measure—which is linked to a different aspect of good cycle provision—is to make alternative cycle routes more numerous, more comfortable, easier to follow, and more convenient (by removi
defaultng annoyances for cyclists, for example).
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultThis said, as reported in the 
defaultCycle Network and Route Planning Guide
default: “
defaultAlternative routes merely supplement the main road routes, and rarely eliminate the need fo
defaultr cycle provision on the latter”; and also: “
defaultIndirect cycle routes may lead cyclists to choose more d
defaultirect routes with greater risk”.
default&#xa0;
defaultFinally, there is no debate between myself and other cycle advocates about where we would like to end up. No, the debate is about where to begin. I have asked them ma
defaultybe a thousand million, billion squillion times why they are not campaigning for the installation of high quality infrastructure to be undertaken within the framework provided by a functioning cycle netw
defaultork. I never do get an answer. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe often hear in this country about how dangerous cycling is, but rather than focus on the removal of a negative, why don’t we try to build on a positive? For 
defaultthe Enthused and Confident 
defaultcyclists, the problem is not so much safety
default, as
default access. 
defaultT
defaulthe bicycle is
default the fastest, most convenient form of transport in the built-up area. If we opened up our one-way streets and parks to cycling, people would respond very positively.
default&#xa0;
defaultI would like to close with a quote from Steffen Rasmussen from the City of Copenhagen. He
default came to give evidence to the GLA eighteen months ago, and the very first thing he said
default—
defaultthe very first thing
default—
defaultwas as follows: “The key word is an holistic approach and then a separation of functions.”
